body_content.explanation: (of an event, place, flight, etc.) having no tickets, seats, etc. available because they have all been sold:
examples: The hotel is already booked up for March 9-16 of next year.
The best restaurants get booked up quickly.

body_content.explanation: (of a person) having arranged to do something on a particular date or at a particular time so they are unable to do anything else:
examples: I'd like to go but I'm booked up until the weekend.
It's hard to find a good plumber who isn't booked up months in advance.
